txt.en: 'I fear we may have only slowed, but not halted, the correspondence between Lang Rhuven and the Morannon. Uruk emissaries and a Black Númenórean ambassador were on route to Lang Rhuven not too long ago. By the time you reach the encampment, they surely will already be discussing plans with the Easterlings.\n\n'You must defeat the emissaries and ambassador so that they do not report back to their superiors!'
Important emissaries and ambassadors from the Black Gate have come to Lang Rhuven.

Uruk emissaries and the Black Númenórean ambassador can be found in Lang Rhuven on the border of Dagorlad.\n\nYou should defeat Uruk emissaries and the Black Númenórean ambassador found in Lang Rhuven.
You have successfully defeated the Uruk emissaries and the Black Númenórean ambassador. With their defeat, the Easterlings are now cut off from those in Mordor who give them orders.
Defeated the Uruk emissaries and the Black Númenórean ambassador.
